properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 8 at 7:40PM CST until February 9 at 6:00PM CST by NWS Quad Cities IA IL
properties.description:
...Accumulating Snow Late Tonight and Sunday...

.A fast moving storm system will bring a round of snow to the
area late tonight and Sunday. Light snow will begin developing
after midnight, however coverage may remain low through much of
the night.

Expect the snow to quickly increase in coverage during the mid
morning as the intensity also increases. From the mid morning
into the early afternoon, moderate to briefly heavy snow is
possible with snowfall rates of a half inch to 1 inch per hour.
The main impacts from the snow will be slippery roads and
significantly reduced visibilities.

* WHAT...Snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 2 to 4
inches.

* WHERE...In Iowa, Buchanan, Delaware and Dubuque Counties. In
Illinois, Jo Daviess and Stephenson Counties.

* WHEN...From midnight tonight to 6 PM CST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions and significantly
reduced visibilities.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The heaviest snow rates are expected to
fall from the mid morning to early afternoon on Sunday. Up to 1
inch per hour is possible.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

In Illinois, go to www.gettingaroundillinois.com for road
conditions. In Iowa, call 511 for road conditions.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM MIDNIGHT TONIGHT TO 6 PM CST SUNDAY
